de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result
Class AlgorithmResultContent

java.lang.Object
  de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result.AlgorithmResultContent
Direct Known Subclasses:
AlgorithmResultContentTreeNode, AlgorithmResultInteractiveContent
public class AlgorithmResultContent
extends Object

The class represents a content which is displayed as part of an AlgorithmResult. You can use a content to display a structure, associated subgraphs and / or element-tips ( for the vertices and / or edges of that structure ). Please notice that you have to specify a structure for each content either by attaching the structure to the content or by attaching the structure to the result, the content belongs to. Subgraphs and element-tips are given together with a description, which has to be identical to the description given for the corresponding subgraph-/element-tip-display-mode of the result the content belongs to. Please see AlgorithmResult for further information about contents and results.

Author:
ordyniak

addElementTips

public void addElementTips(String description,
                           Hashtable elementTips)
Add element-tips to be displayed with this content. Note that there has to be a corresponding element-tip-display-mode with the same description in the AlgorithmResult this content belongs to.

Parameters:
description - a description for this element-tip
elementTips - elementtips should be a Hashtable from vertices and / or edges of the structure ( which is displayed with this content ) to String. When the content is displayed GrALoG paints the Strings as tool-tips on the vertices and / or edges.

getElementTips

protected Hashtable<String,ElementTips> getElementTips(Hashtable<String,ElementTipsDisplayMode> modes)
                                                throws UserException
This method is called by GrALoG when this content is displayed, to infer all element-tips that are registered with this content and correspond to an element-tips-display-mode registered with the corresponding AlgorithmResult. Subclasses can override this method in order to build their element-tips on the fly.

getDisplaySubgraphs

protected Hashtable<String,DisplaySubgraph> getDisplaySubgraphs(Hashtable<String,DisplaySubgraphMode> modes,
                                                                Structure structure)
                                                         throws UserException
This method is called from GrALoG before displaying the content and should return all subgraphs together with their corresponding description that should be displayed with this content. The default method uses the parameter structure to construct all subgraphs for all subgraphInfo's registered with this content. Subclasses can override this method to change the subgraphs that should be displayed by this content or to construct these on the fly.

Parameters:
modes - the displaysubgraphmodes registered with the corresponding AlgorithmResult
structure - the GrALoG-structure needed to construct actual subgraphs from the subgraphInfos registered with this content
Returns:
a Hashtable of subgraphs and their descriptions which should be displayed with this content
Throws:
UserException
